{"title_page": "Dmowski's Line", "text_new": "[[Plik:Polish territorial demands on Paris Peace Conference 1919.png|thumb|300px|Polish territorial demands on Paris Peace Conference 1919 (Dmowski's Line) on ethnographical background and borders of [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian Commonwealth]] 1772]]\n[[File:Liniadmowskiego.png|thumb|180px|Dmowski's Line]]\n'''Dmowski's Line''' ({{lang-pl|Linia Dmowskiego}}) was a proposed border of Poland after World War I. It was proposed by the Polish delegation at the [[Paris Peace Conference, 1919|Paris Peace Conference]] of 1919 and it was named after [[Roman Dmowski]], Polish foreign minister. Poland wanted [[Upper Silesia]], [[Pomerelia]] including [[Danzig]], [[Warmia]] and [[Masuria]], all of [[Lithuania]], and western parts of [[Belarus]], [[Polesia]], [[Volhynia]] and [[Podolia]].\n\n==Boundary line==\nThe boundary line to the east was Polish by the notes from the Polish Delegation as follows:<ref>[http://www.ibidem.com.pl/zrodla/1918-1939/polityka/miedzynarodowa/1919-03-03-nota-granice-wschodnie.html Ibidem - Zrodla do historii Polski XIX - XX w]</ref>\n\n{{quote|...&nbsp;ranging from the Baltic coast east of \u0141abiawy boundary line follows the coast to the north of Klaip\u0117da and Palanga.&nbsp;... From the coast to the north of Libawa proceed to the east boundary line of the historic border between the Poland 1772, and Courland. It comes in this way to the I\u0142\u0142ukszta county in Courland. This county is recovered by Poland due to its geographical position and the advantage of the Polish element in the population. From here, border proceeds along the limit of I\u0142\u0142ukszta county to Daugava river and passes on its right bank (Vitebsk Governorate) in order to proceed eastward parallel to the river, and approximately 30 kilometers to the borders of the Dry\u015bwiaty county, including same, along with the [[Polock]] county. Next it passes the north-west from Horodka, returns to the left bank of the Daugava River about 30 miles west of Vitebsk and goes toward the south, passing west of the Sienna to the point where it meets the boundary between Minsk and Mohylow Gouvernement, proceeding from the boundary line towards the south until the Berezina in place where it touches the northern border of the Rzeczyca county, then crossing the Berezina, goes in a southwesterly direction to the marshes to the east of Mazyr. From there, crossing Pripyat, the boundary follows the dividing line between the Rzeczyca and Mazyr counties, then, is still proceeding in a south west, passes to the west to the cities of Zwiahel and Ovruch in Volhynia and arrives at the point where the borders of Zaslaw, Ostrog and Zwiahel counties meet. Then, heading south, the frontier line is progressing along the eastern border of Zaslaw and Starokonstantyn\u00f3w counties, to the point where it meets boundaries of Latycz\u00f3w and Ploskir\u00f3w counties in Podolia, there is still in a southerly direction until it reaches the river Uszyca near Zi\u0144k\u00f3w and goes along its course to the Dniester, which is at this point the southern border between Poland and Romania.}} \n\nThis proposal was rejected, and later withdrawn by the author, Roman Dmowski, who, during the negotiations ending the Polish-Bolshevik war, spoke out against the inclusion of Minsk. He explained the desire to build a country without ethnic minorities; the de facto theme was the desire to prevent the concept of [[Mi\u0119dzymorze|federation (Mi\u0119dzymorze)]] of [[Jozef Pilsudski]], even to a limited extent. Consequently, in the [[Treaty of Riga]] the Polish-Soviet border was demarcated in the distance of about 30&nbsp;km to the west and north of Minsk. Polish territory according to Dmowski's proposal was supposed to be equal to 447,000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.<ref>[http://zso1.olsztyn.pl/~publikacje/gran_mstep.doc Kszta\u0142towanie si\u0119 granic Polski po I Wojnie \u015awiatowej] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719103706/http://zso1.olsztyn.pl/~publikacje/gran_mstep.doc |date=July 19, 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Mi\u0119dzymorze]]\n* [[Curzon Line]]\n* [[Foch Line]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.ibidem.com.pl/zrodla/1918-1939/polityka/miedzynarodowa/1919-02-28-nota-granice-zachodnie.html Polish Note on Peace Conference (western borders)]\n* [http://www.ibidem.com.pl/zrodla/1918-1939/polityka/miedzynarodowa/1919-03-03-nota-granice-wschodnie.html Polish Note on Peace Conference (eastern borders)]\n\n[[Category:Second Polish Republic]]\n[[Category:Borders of Poland]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Liniadmowskiego.png|thumb|180px|Dmowski's Line]]\n'''Dmowski's Line''' ({{lang-pl|Linia Dmowskiego}}) was a proposed border of Poland after World War I. It was proposed by the Polish delegation at the [[Paris Peace Conference, 1919|Paris Peace Conference]] of 1919 and it was named after [[Roman Dmowski]], Polish foreign minister. Poland wanted [[Upper Silesia]], [[Pomerelia]] including [[Danzig]], [[Warmia]] and [[Masuria]], all of [[Lithuania]], and western parts of [[Belarus]], [[Polesia]], [[Volhynia]] and [[Podolia]].\n\n==Boundary line==\nThe boundary line to the east was Polish by the notes from the Polish Delegation as follows:<ref>[http://www.ibidem.com.pl/zrodla/1918-1939/polityka/miedzynarodowa/1919-03-03-nota-granice-wschodnie.html Ibidem - Zrodla do historii Polski XIX - XX w]</ref>\n\n{{quote|...&nbsp;ranging from the Baltic coast east of \u0141abiawy boundary line follows the coast to the north of Klaip\u0117da and Palanga.&nbsp;... From the coast to the north of Libawa proceed to the east boundary line of the historic border between the Poland 1772, and Courland. It comes in this way to the I\u0142\u0142ukszta county in Courland. This county is recovered by Poland due to its geographical position and the advantage of the Polish element in the population. From here, border proceeds along the limit of I\u0142\u0142ukszta county to Daugava river and passes on its right bank (Vitebsk Governorate) in order to proceed eastward parallel to the river, and approximately 30 kilometers to the borders of the Dry\u015bwiaty county, including same, along with the [[Polock]] county. Next it passes the north-west from Horodka, returns to the left bank of the Daugava River about 30 miles west of Vitebsk and goes toward the south, passing west of the Sienna to the point where it meets the boundary between Minsk and Mohylow Gouvernement, proceeding from the boundary line towards the south until the Berezina in place where it touches the northern border of the Rzeczyca county, then crossing the Berezina, goes in a southwesterly direction to the marshes to the east of Mazyr. From there, crossing Pripyat, the boundary follows the dividing line between the Rzeczyca and Mazyr counties, then, is still proceeding in a south west, passes to the west to the cities of Zwiahel and Ovruch in Volhynia and arrives at the point where the borders of Zaslaw, Ostrog and Zwiahel counties meet. Then, heading south, the frontier line is progressing along the eastern border of Zaslaw and Starokonstantyn\u00f3w counties, to the point where it meets boundaries of Latycz\u00f3w and Ploskir\u00f3w counties in Podolia, there is still in a southerly direction until it reaches the river Uszyca near Zi\u0144k\u00f3w and goes along its course to the Dniester, which is at this point the southern border between Poland and Romania.}} \n\nThis proposal was rejected, and later withdrawn by the author, Roman Dmowski, who, during the negotiations ending the Polish-Bolshevik war, spoke out against the inclusion of Minsk. He explained the desire to build a country without ethnic minorities; the de facto theme was the desire to prevent the concept of [[Mi\u0119dzymorze|federation (Mi\u0119dzymorze)]] of [[Jozef Pilsudski]], even to a limited extent. Consequently, in the [[Treaty of Riga]] the Polish-Soviet border was demarcated in the distance of about 30&nbsp;km to the west and north of Minsk. Polish territory according to Dmowski's proposal was supposed to be equal to 447,000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.<ref>[http://zso1.olsztyn.pl/~publikacje/gran_mstep.doc Kszta\u0142towanie si\u0119 granic Polski po I Wojnie \u015awiatowej] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719103706/http://zso1.olsztyn.pl/~publikacje/gran_mstep.doc |date=July 19, 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Mi\u0119dzymorze]]\n* [[Curzon Line]]\n* [[Foch Line]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.ibidem.com.pl/zrodla/1918-1939/polityka/miedzynarodowa/1919-02-28-nota-granice-zachodnie.html Polish Note on Peace Conference (western borders)]\n* [http://www.ibidem.com.pl/zrodla/1918-1939/polityka/miedzynarodowa/1919-03-03-nota-granice-wschodnie.html Polish Note on Peace Conference (eastern borders)]\n\n[[Category:Second Polish Republic]]\n[[Category:Borders of Poland]]\n", "name_user": "Andros64", "label": "safe", "comment": "map", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dmowski%27s_Line"}
{"title_page": "List of wars involving Canada", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a '''list of wars involving Canada'''. The following list includes conflicts involving Canada, or the colonies that made up the country prior to [[Canadian confederation]] in 1867.\n\n==List==\n===Colonial conflicts (17th century\u20131867)===\nThe following were conflicts that occurred in present-day Canada from the 17th century to mid-19th century, prior to [[Canadian confederation]]. Belligerents in these conflicts typically involved colonies that existed in Canada (i.e. [[New France]], [[the Canadas]], etc.), and/or First Nations groups residing in these region. \n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n|-\n! Conflict\n! Combatant 1\n! Combatant 2\n! Result\n|-\n| [[Beaver Wars]]<br>(1609\u20131701)\n| [[Iroqouis]]\n| [[Algonquian peoples|Algonquian]] allies\n| '''Military stalemate'''\n* [[Great Peace of Montreal]]\n* Growth of French influence in the Great Lakes region\n* Huron-Wendat Confederacy destroyed or assimilated\n* Military refugee migration results in expansion of Iroquois hunting grounds\n* Further Iroquois territorial expansion halted in military campaigns by the [[Council of Three Fires]]\n|-\n| [[King William's War]]<br>(1688\u20131697)\n| {{flag|Kingdom of France}}\n* {{flag|New France}}\n[[Wabanaki Confederacy]]\n| {{flag|England}}\n* {{flagdeco|England}} [[British America|English America]]\n[[Iroquois]]\n|'''''Status quo ante bellum'''''\n|-\n| [[Queen Anne's War]]<br>(1702\u20131713)\n| {{flag|Kingdom of France}}\n* {{flag|New France}}\n{{flag|Spain|1701}}<br>[[Wabanaki Confederacy]]<br>[[Mohawk people|Caughnawaga Mohawk]]<br>[[Choctaw]]<br>[[Timucua]]<br>[[Apalachee]]<br>[[Natchez people|Natchez]]\n| {{flag|England}} <small>(before 1707)</small>\n* {{flagdeco|England}} [[British America|English America]]\n{{flag|Great Britain|1707}} <small>(after 1707)</small>\n* {{flagdeco|British Empire|1707}} [[British America]]\n[[Muscogee people|Muscogee]]<br>[[Chickasaw]]<br>[[Yamasee]]\n----\n[[Iroquois Confederacy]]\n|'''British-Allied victory'''\n* France cedes to Britain the control of Acadia, Newfoundland, Hudson Bay, and Saint Kitts\n|-\n| [[Dummer's War]]<br>(1722\u20131725)\n| [[New England Colonies]]<br>[[Mohawk people|Mohawk]]\n| [[Wabanaki Confederacy]]<br>[[Abenaki]]<br>[[Pequawket]]<br>[[Mi'kmaq]]<br>[[Maliseet]]\n|\n|-\n| [[King George's War]]<br>(1744\u20131748)\n| {{flag|Kingdom of France}}\n* {{flag|New France}}\n[[Wabanaki Confederacy]]\n| {{flag|British Empire|1707}}\n* {{flagdeco|British Empire|1707}} [[British America]]\n[[Iroquois Confederacy]] \n| '''''Status quo ante bellum'''''\n|-\n| [[Father Le Loutre's War]]<br>(1749\u20131755)\n|[[Wabanaki Confederacy]] \n* [[Mi'kmaq militia]] \n* [[Military history of the Maliseet people|Maliseet militia]]\n{{flag|Kingdom of France}}\n* {{flag|New France}}\n* [[Acadian militia]]\n| {{flag|British Empire|1707}}\n* {{flagdeco|British Empire|1707}} Nova Scotia\n|'''British victory'''\n* Beginning of the [[expulsion of the Acadians]] in 1755\n|-\n| [[French and Indian War]]<br>(1756\u20131763)\n| {{flag|Kingdom of France}}\n* {{flag|New France}}\n[[Wabanaki Confederacy]]<br>[[Abenaki]]<br>[[Mi'kmaq militia]]<br>[[Acadian militia]]<br>[[Algonquian peoples|Algonquin]]<br>[[Lenape]]<br>[[Ojibwa]]<br>[[Odawa]]<br>[[Shawnee]]\n| {{flag|British Empire|1707}}\n* {{flagdeco|British Empire|1707}} [[British America]]\n[[Iroquois Confederacy]]<br>[[Catawba people|Catawba]]<br>[[Cherokee]] (before 1758)\n|'''British-Allied victory'''\n* British [[Conquest of New France (1758-1760)|military conquest of New France]]\n* France cedes New France east of the Mississippi River to Great Britain, retaining Saint Pierre and Miquelon, and transfers Louisiana to Spain\n|-\n| [[American Revolutionary War]]<br/>(1775\u20131783)\n| {{flag|British Empire|1707}}\n* {{flagdeco|British Empire|1707}} [[Province of Quebec (1763\u20131791)|Province of Quebec]]\n* {{flagdeco|British Empire|1707}} Nova Scotia\n| {{flag|United States|1795}}<br>{{flagcountry|Kingdom of France}}<br>{{flagcountry|Spain|1748}}\n| '''American-Allied victory'''\n* Incursions into [[Invasion of Quebec (1775)|Quebec]] and [[Nova Scotia in the American Revolution|Nova Scotia]] repulsed\n* Great Britain cedes to the United States the area east of the Mississippi River and south of the Great Lakes and St. Lawrence River\n* Great Britain cedes East Florida, West Florida, and Menorca to Spain\n|-\n| [[War of 1812]]<br/>(1812\u20131815)\n| {{flag|British Empire}}\n* {{flag|Lower Canada|size=23px}}\n* {{flag|Upper Canada|size=23px}}\n[[Tecumseh's Confederacy]]<br>[[Shawnee]]<br>[[Ojibwe]]<br>[[Meskwaki|Fox]]<br>[[Iroquois]]<br>[[Miami people|Miami]]<br>[[Mingo]]<br>[[Odawa]]<br>[[Kickapoo people|Kickapoo]]<br>[[Lenape]]<br>[[Mascouten]]<br>[[Potawatomi]]<br>[[Sauk people|Sauk]]<br>[[Wyandot people|Wyandot]]<br>{{flag|Spain|1785}} <small>(1814)</small>\n| {{flag|United States|1775}}\n[[Choctaw]]<br>[[Cherokee]]<br>[[Muscogee]]<br>[[Seneca people|Seneca]]\n| '''''Status quo ante bellum'''''\n* Military stalemate\n|-\n| [[Rebellions of 1837\u20131838]]<br/>(1837&ndash;1838)\n| {{flag|Lower Canada|size=23px}}<br />[[Ch\u00e2teau Clique]]\n-------\n{{flag|Upper Canada|size=23px}}<br />[[Family Compact]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Patriote movement (Lower Canada).svg|size=23px}} [[Patriotes]]<br />{{nowrap|{{flagicon image|Flag of the Patriote movement (Lower Canada).svg|size=23px}} [[Republic of Lower Canada]]}}\n----------\n[[Hunters' Lodges]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Republic of Canada.svg|size=23px}} [[Republic of Canada]]\n| '''Victory'''\n* Patriote rebellion crushed by loyalist forces; Republic of Canada dismantled\n* Defeat of Hunters' Lodges\n* Unification of Upper and Lower Canada into the Province of Canada\n|}\n===Confederated Canada (1867\u2013present)===\nThe following table lists conflicts involving Canada following [[Canadian confederation]] in 1867.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:red; color:white;\" | Conflict\n! style=\"background-color:red; color:white;\" | Combatant 1\n! style=\"background-color:red; color:white;\" | Combatant 2\n! style=\"background-color:red; color:white;\" | Result\n! style=\"background-color:red; color:white;\" | Killed\n! style=\"background-color:red; color:white;\" | Wounded\n|-\n|-\n| [[Fenian Raids]]<br/>(1866&ndash;1871)\n| {{flag|Canada|1868|size=23px}}{{notetag|Raids conducted in 1866 occurred in the [[Province of Canada]], and the colony of New Brunswick, prior to Canadian confederation}}\n| {{flagicon image|Green harp flag of Ireland.svg|size=23px}} [[Fenian Brotherhood]]\n| '''Victory'''\n* Fenians cease raids\n| '''22'''\n| '''32'''\n|-\n| [[Wolseley Expedition]]<br/>(1870)\n| {{flag|Canada|1868|size=23px}}\n| {{flagicon image|Metis Blue.svg|size=23px}} [[M\u00e9tis people (Canada)|M\u00e9tis]]\n| '''Victory'''\n* [[Red River Rebellion]] defeated\n* The legislature passes the [[Manitoba Act]] in 1870\n* [[Red River Colony]] enters Canada as the province of [[Manitoba]]\n| '''None'''\n| '''None'''\n|-\n| [[Mahdist War]]<br/>(1881&ndash;1899)\n| {{flagcountry|United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Canada|1868|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagicon|Egypt|1882|size=23px}} [[Khedivate of Egypt|Egypt]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Mahdist Revolt.svg|size=23px}} [[History of Mahdist Sudan|Sudan]]\n| '''Victory'''\n* Sudan becomes the [[Anglo-Egyptian Sudan]], a [[Condominium (international law)|condominium]] of the [[British Empire]]\n| '''16'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.ca/en/article/nile-expedition|title=Nile Expedition|work=[[The Canadian Encyclopedia]]}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| [[North-West Rebellion]]<br/>(1885)\n| {{flag|Canada|1868|size=23px}}\n| [[Provisional Government of Saskatchewan]] ([[M\u00e9tis people (Canada)|M\u00e9tis]])<br />[[Cree]]\u2013[[Assiniboine people|Assiniboine]]\n| '''Victory'''\n* Completion of the [[Canadian Pacific Railway]]\n* [[Trial of Louis Riel]]\n| '''26'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://peel.library.ualberta.ca/bibliography/1519/15.html}}</ref>\n| '''103'''\n|-\n| [[Second Boer War]]<br/>(1899&ndash;1902)\n| {{flagcountry|United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Canada|1868|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Australia|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|New Zealand|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|British Raj|name=India|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|British Ceylon|name=Ceylon|size=23px}}<br/>[[File:Flag of the Cape Colony 1876-1910.svg|23px|border|link=]] [[British Cape Colony|Cape Colony]]<br/>[[File:Flag of the Natal Colony 1875-1910.svg|23px|border|link=]] [[Natal Colony]]<br/>[[File:Flag of BSAC edit.svg|23px|border|link=]] [[Company rule in Rhodesia|Rhodesia]]\n| {{flag|Orange Free State|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|South African Republic|size=23px}}\n| '''Victory'''\n* British sovereignty over the Orange Free State and the Transvaal in accordance with the [[Treaty of Vereeniging]]\n| '''267'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.warmuseum.ca/cwm/exhibitions/boer/boerwarhistory_e.shtml}}</ref>\n| '''>250'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.veterans.gc.ca/eng/remembrance/history/south-african-war/canada-in-the-south-african-war}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[First World War]]<br/>(1914&ndash;1918)\n| {{flagcountry|French Third Republic|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Russian Empire|name=Russia|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|United States|1912|size=23px}}<br />{{flagicon|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|1912|size=23px}} [[Beiyang Government|China]]<br />{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Empire of Japan|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Canada|1907|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Newfoundland|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Australia|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|New Zealand|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|British Raj|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Union of South Africa|1912|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Serbia|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Montenegro|size=23px}}<br /> {{flagcountry|Kingdom of Romania|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Belgium|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Greece|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Portugal|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Brazil|size=23px}}\n| {{flagcountry|German Empire|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Austria-Hungary|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Ottoman Empire|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Bulgaria|size=23px}}\n| '''Victory'''\n* End of the [[German Empire|German]], [[Russian Empire|Russian]], [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]], and [[Austria-Hungary|Austro-Hungarian]] empires\n* Formation of new countries in Europe and the Middle East\n* Transfer of [[German colonies]] and [[Partitioning of the Ottoman Empire|regions of the former Ottoman Empire]] to other powers\n* Establishment of the [[League of Nations]]\n| '''66,944'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.centre-robert-schuman.org/userfiles/files/REPERES%20%E2%80%93%20module%201-1-1%20-%20explanatory%20notes%20%E2%80%93%20World%20War%20I%20casualties%20%E2%80%93%20EN.pdf}}</ref>\n| '''~172,000'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.veterans.gc.ca/eng/remembrance/history/first-world-war}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Allied intervention in the Russian Civil War|Russian Civil War]]<br/>(1918&ndash;1920)\n| {{flagicon|Russia|size=23px}} [[White Movement]]<br/>{{flag|France|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagcountry|United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|United States|1912|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagicon|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|1912|size=23px}} [[Beiyang Government|China]]<br/>{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagcountry|Empire of Japan|name=Japan|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Canada|1907|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Australia|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|British Raj|name=India|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Union of South Africa|name=South Africa|1912|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Serbia|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Romania|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Greece|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Czechoslovakia|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Poland|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Estonia|size=23px}}\n| {{flag|Russian SFSR|1918|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Far Eastern Republic|size=23px}}<br>{{flagicon image|Flag of Latvian SSR 1919.svg|size=23px}} [[Latvian Socialist Soviet Republic|Latvian SSR]]<br/>{{flagicon image|Flag of the Ukrainian SSR (1923-1927).svg|size=23px}} [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic|Ukrainian SSR]]<br/>{{flagicon image|Flag of the Commune of the Working People of Estonia.svg|size=23px}} [[Commune of the Working People of Estonia|Commune of Estonia]]<br/>{{flagicon image|Flag of the People's Republic of Mongolia (1921-1924).svg|size=23px}} [[Mongolian People's Party|Mongolian Communists]]\n| '''Defeat'''\n* Allied withdrawal from Russia\n* Bolshevik victory over [[White Movement|White Army]]\n* The [[Soviet Union]] becomes the new Russian power\n| '''14'''\n| '''24'''\n|-\n| [[Second World War]]<br/>(1939&ndash;1945)\n| {{flag|Soviet Union|1936|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|United States|1912|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|United Kingdom|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|name=China|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|France|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Poland|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Canada|1921|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Australia|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|New Zealand|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|British Raj|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Union of South Africa|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Yugoslavia|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Greece|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Denmark|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Norway|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Netherlands|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Belgium|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Luxembourg|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Czechoslovakia|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Brazil|1889|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Mexico|1934|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Ethiopian Empire|size=23px}}\n| {{flagcountry|Nazi Germany|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Empire of Japan|size=23px}}<br />{{fla